headline: Jobless Claims Rise Remain Near Historic Low
summary: On Thursday, the Labor Departmentreportedthat initial unemployment claims rose to 206,000 last week.  The number was higher than expected but still remained near the lowest level in decades.Employers remain hesitant to lay off workers in the face of a tight labor supply.  The labor force participation rate was 61.8% in November, compared to 63.3% in February, and the size of the civilian labor force is down by 2.4 million.
